      "content": "The \"Neutral-Score\" system is already being finalized in our dev environment, so we are moving forward with it. Can you explain why you think a reduction in predictive accuracy is inevitable? Specifically, if we strip out those proxy variables to ensure we aren't unfairly penalizing specific ethnic groups, what exactly is lost in the prediction?",
